commit.message: Prepare for release 0.72
Remove old perl versions not supported by Travis CI
Don't use C "for" syntax
Add sample script to reproduce bug in #github49.

auth: report a generic error on failure.

auth was leaving the error status as set by the last authentication
method tried which could be very confusing.

Not a generic method (LIBSSH2_ERROR_AUTHENTICATION_FAILED) is used.

Picking a crypto backend from the command line was not working.

Argument parsing was done too late, and Module::Install was chocking
on the `gcrypt` or `openssl` argument.

Fix strings for converting error codes to error names.

Error code LIBSSH2_ERROR_PUBLICKEY_UNRECOGNIZED has been renamed to
LIBSSH2_ERROR_AUTHENTICATION_FAILED and is used now in a more general
way.

Two new errors have also been added.
Pod::Simple is missing from travis environment
Add testing for libssh2 1.8.0 back (current version in Ubuntu)
update perl and libssh2 versions used for testing in travis

commit.message:
Move bugs queue to github issues.

Set the bugtracker resource to github issues to replace the default RT.

People would still be able to use RT, but things like the Issues link on
metacpan.org would point to github issues instead.

for dll import libs, as this fails on the MSYS2 MinGW perl.

commit.message: Fix spelling error in manpage for Net::SSH2

remove extra test for deadline

This line follows the same test four lines above.

At best, this line does nothing, since it is only tested if the previous
test failed, so this test will almost always fail too.

At worst, the timing will be exactly right for the first test to fail
and the second test to pass, which would result in a return without
setting the "Time out" error.

Mac installation fixes.

Support using brew from any prefix.

Use brew --prefix to get the prefixes of openssl and libssh2 and add
them to the search paths.

Suppress the Can't exec "ldd" error message (macOS does not have ldd.)

- Fix #50

Signed-off-by: Rafael Kitover <rkitover@gmail.com>
TravisCI: check against libssh2 1.8.1 and perl 2.28
doc improvements
Fix TravisCI testing: require a recent Module::Install
